captions.text:
Hi, this isJulia Child
with a tip on making
crepes Suzette,

that marvelous
flaming dessert
that you do at the table.

You need a nice flaming setup.
l've got a heat source there.

ln the pan l have a mixture
ofsugar, butter, orangejuice
and grated orange peel.

l'm taking a crepe,
and l'm bathing it
in this mixture--

[TV: Child ]
l like to use a no-stick pan
and heat until water--

Let it bubble up well,
and then dip it
intoyour flames--

Little problem
in the kitchen.
Nothing trivial.

Actually,
i t's a l i ttle overdone
for my taste.

You don't want to
tell me what happened ?

l just want to relax
in a nice lukewarm bath.

[Walter]
l don't think
that can hurt us anymore.

I'll never understand this style of comedy.

This is a movie about a good couple getting MAJORLY FUCKED FROM EVERY 
DIRECTION POSSIBLE and diving into a financial hell while being surrounded 
by retarded people.

I was hoping Tom Hanks would kill himself to get people to understand how 
absolutely retarded they were being, but instead we get this "golly geee~ 
how will i get out of this" reaction, which is somehow supposed to be 
funny? I can't go through an hour of frustration and forget about it 
because of a good ending.﻿
